  <TITLE>semi  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="semi (;)"> instruction and row separator  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    semicolons  are used to separate rows in a matrix definition.
  </P>
  <P>
    semicolons may also be used at the end of an instruction. In this
    case it means that the result(s) are not displayed. Conversely use
    comma (,) to get the display
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
a=[1,2,3;4,5,6];
a=1;b=1,c=2
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
